http://code.google.com/p/libgdx/issues/detail?id=1556

Made some best guesses on whether the loaders are expecting relative or absolute pathing. SkinLoader.java would be my main worry, but if there is a bug it is as simple as changing the boolean :-)

Example of an Absolute FileHandleResolver created using this setup:

```
import com.badlogic.gdx.Gdx;
import com.badlogic.gdx.assets.loaders.FileHandleResolver;
import com.badlogic.gdx.files.FileHandle;

public class AbsoluteFileHandleResolver implements FileHandleResolver {
    public AbsoluteFileHandleResolver() {
    }

    @Override
    public FileHandle resolve(String fileName, boolean relative) {
        if(relative){
            return Gdx.files.absolute(fileName);
        } else {
            return Gdx.files.absolute("C:/Users/Dave/Game/" + fileName);
        }
    }
}
```
